<p class="title" style="text-align: center;">LEAGUE OVERVIEW &nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align: center;">The purpose of these bylaws is to (1) ensure a fair and fun league for all owners, (2) &nbsp;promote the long-term viability of the league. </p>
<p style="text-align: center;"> If a rule is not explicitly stated, &nbsp;interpretations will consider these criteria and new rules will be voted on and &nbsp;subsequently documented in these bylaws.</p> 
<p style="text-align: center;">If this document disagrees with league &nbsp;site settings, site settings will prevail until corrected. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• 12 teams in 2 divisions playing a 13 game schedule with 3 weeks of playoffs.</p>
<p>&nbsp;• 25 roster spots (9 playable, 18 bench</p>
<p>• 3 Taxi&nbsp;(Practice Squad) Roster Slots &nbsp;</p>
<p>• 2 IR (Injured Reserve) Roster Slot &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Starters - QB / 2RB / 2WR / TE / 1Flex(RB/WR/TE) /1 K /1 Def &nbsp;</p>
<p>• An initial startup draft will be conducted on ____</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>• A four (4) round rookie draft complete before the start of the NFL preseason </p>
<p>• Post startup rookie draft order determined by reverse order of standings. </p>
<p>• A position-balanced 1 PPR scoring system(See Scoring) &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Free agents acquired by Blind Bid Auction processed on Wednesdays. &nbsp;Dropped players and all free agents after game start will be placed on &nbsp;waivers. Dropped players will spend a minimum of 24 hours on the waiver &nbsp;wire. After waivers, the remaining free agents are available by First Come &nbsp;First Serve claims. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Three-week, six-team playoff structure running NFL weeks 14-16. Two top teams by record get a bye. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Trading prohibited from the beginning of NFL Week 11 to the end of NFL Week &nbsp;16. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Consolation bracket (“Toilet Bowl”) for six non-playoff teams running NFL &nbsp;weeks 14-16. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• $***&nbsp;annual league dues. &nbsp;</p>
<p>• Prize pools with payouts as following: 1st prize=****, less league expenses</p>
<p>• The league is designed to run for decades with smooth ownership transitions &nbsp;if necessary. Rules may be modified by league vote to achieve overarching goals. </p>
